<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--LaxativeCake     03-10 0122</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Laxative Cake,0124</SECOND>
<HEAD>Party prank leads to jail</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANITOWOC, Wis. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A taxi company owner and his wife who
jokingly spiked a party cake with a laxative have been sentenced to
75 days in jail on a battery conviction.
   Martin Yauch, 38, and Lois M. Yauch, 40, originally charged with
placing a foreign substance in edibles, pleaded guilty in November
to a reduced charge of misdemeanor battery. They were sentenced
Thursday.
   Investigators said the couple placed a commercial laxative in a
cake at a company party in May 1987 as a prank. Some employees
became ill but none required hospitalization.
   The Circuit Court jail sentence involves the state's Huber Law,
under which the couple can leave jail during working hours.
</TEXT>
