Rice University on a football scholarship and hoped to be a
professional football player until World War II came along.
   He joined the U.S. Army Air Corps, hoping to be a pilot, but
became a bombardier after washing out as a pilot candidate.
   Beahan retired from the U.S. Air Force as a lieutenant colonel in
1963 and worked for Brown &amp; Root Inc. as a technical writer until he
retired in 1985.
