<HEAD>Ten Killed In Gold Mine Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ten men were killed and 22
injured in a fire at a gold mine that occurred more than a mile
underground, a mining company said today.
   Anglo-American Corp. said the fire broke out Thursday evening at
the Vaal Reef Gold Mine outside Johannesburg in a shaft 1.3 miles
below ground.
