the Syrian government, stressing that we hold it responsible for the
safety of our diplomatic personnel,'' she said.
   ``We once again urge Syria to take action against the PFLP-GC
terrorist group to insure that there is no repetition of such
incidents and that it end its activities,'' Ms. Beck said.
   ``Because the PFLP-GC is headquartered in Damascus, Syria must
bear responsibility for its actions,'' she said.
   The PFLP-GC is a faction formed by Ahmed Jibril, an officer in
the Syrian army, in 1968. Most of its attacks have been against
