State's Attorney, in the Feb. 28 mayoral primary, was courted
privately earlier this week by both Daley and Alderman Timothy
Evans, who bypassed the primary to run as an independent in the
April 4 special election.
   Sawyer delayed an announcement on an endorsement until next week,
but said he probably will remain neutral.
   The April 4 election will choose a successor to serve out the
final two years of Mayor Harold Washington's second term. Washington
died of a heart attack in November 1987.
