<HEAD>Going For Realism, Stallone Injures Knee</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actor Sylvester Stallone injured his knee while
filming some football sequences for his new movie and had it checked
at an orthopedic hospital, his publicist said Friday.
   ``The doctor told him his football career is probably over,''
joked Andrea Jaffe. ``No, really, he's fine. He just went to the
hospital. He wasn't rushed there or anything. ... They just bandaged
it up and he's going back to work.''
   Jaffe said Stallone, 42, was shooting scenes for his new movie
``Hard Time'' at Rahway State Prison in New Jersey on Wednesday and
refused to use a double during the hard-hitting sequence which has
inmates playing football, sans protective equipment.
   ``They were doing a lot of tight shots and he was going for that
realism, so he wanted to do it himself,'' Jaffe said. ``He took a
hard hit.''
   The next day when he woke up, his knee was stiff and he went to a
Manhattan hospital to have doctors look at it.
   She said he had no scenes to shoot on Thursday but would be at
work Friday night.
</TEXT>
