<FIRST>r w AM-TreasuryBills     03-10 0091</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Treasury Bills,90</SECOND>
<HEAD>T-Bills Up</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Interest rates on 52-week Treasury bills rose
in Thursday's action to the highest level in four years.
   The Treasury Department sold $9 billion of the bills at an
average discount rate of 8.68 percent, up from 8.59 percent at the
last auction on Feb. 14.
   The rates were the highest since March 14, 1985, when the
one-year bills sold for 9.24 percent. The new discount rate
understates the actual return to investors _ 9.43 percent with a
$10,000 bill selling for $9,122.40.
