<HEAD>Remarks by Bush and Cheney as President Picks Congressman for Defense
Post</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a transcript of remarks Friday by
President Bush and Rep. Richard Cheney as the president announced
his selection of the Republican congressman from Wyoming to be
secretary of defense and they answered reporters' questions.
   Bush: Well, good afternoon.
   I am happy to be here this afternoon to present my nominee to be
secretary of defense: Congressman Dick Cheney of Wyoming.
   Dick is a widely respected man of principle, served his country
with distinction for many years.
   I have known him as a chief of staff, government manager, all
under President Ford, '75 and '76.
   I worked with him closely as he's been a part of the Republican
leadership.
