<FIRST>u i AM-Germany-FailedEscape     03-10 0240</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Germany-Failed Escape,0245</SECOND>
<HEAD>Guards Open Fire To Foil Escape Attempt; Balloonist Killed In Other
Try</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BERLIN (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   East German border guards opened fire as three
people tried to escape from the communist sector to West Berlin on
Friday, apparently wounding one person and arresting the two others,
police said.
   West Berlin police said the East German guards were seen carrying
away one bleeding person after firing several shots Friday afternoon
at the three who tried to reach the wall. The two others were also
captured by the guards but it was not known if they were hit by the
shots.
   Police said the escape attempt in the Spandau district was foiled
while the three were still on a strip of land between the first line
of East German border barriers and the wall.
   Police could not give any other details.
   Communist guards shot and killed a 22-year-old East German man
Feb. 6 as he tried to scale the Berlin Wall with a ladder.
   A 32-year-old East German man fell to his death from a homemade
hot air balloon after flying over the Berlin Wall on Wednesday. West
Berlin police said the man fell from a considerable height and that
there was no evidence the balloon might have been shot down by East
German guards.
   U.S. military mission spokesman Anthony Sariti, speaking for all
three Western Allies in West Berlin, called on East Germany to tear
down the wall.
