<FIRST>d a AM-BRF--Slow-SpeedChase     03-10 0160</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Slow-Speed Chase,0164</SECOND>
<HEAD>Slow Chase on Interstate Ends in Suspect's Death</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A chase that never exceeded 20 mph ended
in death for a 25-year-old man when his car collided head-on with an
18-wheel truck Thursday, police said.
   An officer began pursuing Eddie Lynn Spencer of Kilgore when he
was spotted driving erratically about 3 a.m. on Interstate 20,
police said.
   Forest Hill officer Clint Turner told investigators he saw the
car stop three times, and that it never went faster than 20 mph, but
when he tried to pull it over, the driver kept going and began
weaving.
   The suspect finally pulled over, but the car bolted when Turner
approached, police said.
   Spencer made a U-turn to go west in an eastbound lane and after
800 yards he collided with the truck. The truck driver was uninjured
and not charged, police said.
   Police said an autopsy would determine if alcohol contributed to
the crash.
</TEXT>
