<HEAD>With PM-Eastern Rdp, Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are the biggest companies to file petitions for Chapter 11
bankruptcy protection, their assets, when they filed and their
status.
   _ Texaco Inc., assets $35 billion, April 1987. Emerged April 1988.
   _ Baldwin-United Corp., $9.38 billion, September 1983. Emerged
November 1986 as PHLCORP.
   _ Penn Central Corp., $7 billion, 1970. Emerged October 1978.
   _ LTV Corp., $6 billion, July 17, 1986, pending.
   _ Eastern Airlines, $4.5 billion, March 1989, pending.
   _ Public Service Company of New Hampshire, $3 billion, Jan. 28,
1988, pending.
   _ Manville Corp., $2 billion, August 1982. Emerged Janary 1989.
   _ Wickes Cos., $2 billion, April 1982. Emerged January 1985.
   _ Wheeling-Pittsburgh Steel Corp., $1 billion, April 16, 1985,
pending.
   _ Storage Technology Corp., $1 billion, October 1984. Emerged
July 1987.
   _ Allegheny International Inc., $745 million, 1988, pending.
   _ A.H. Robins Co., $453.1 million, Aug. 21, 1985, pending.
