<HEAD>London Shares Higher In Active Trading</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices were higher at midday Friday, with
players saying they were surprised by the strength of the market,
particularly ahead of the release of U.S. unemployment figures and
the weak performance on Wall Street Thursday.
   Dealers said they couldn't account for the buoyant tone of
trading.
   ``It's astonishingly firm,'' said one market maker. ``I can't say
why but we did feel a buzz of excitement this morning.''
   Electrical stocks were a main feature, dealers said, with
reported strong demand from the United States.
   At about 12:15 p.m., the Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share
index was 13.8 points, or 0.7 percent, higher at 2,089.7, and just a
shade below its late-morning best level of 2,090.4. The market
opened at its 2,082.3 low point.
   Volume amounted to a moderate 377 million shares, compared with
272.9 million shares at the same time on Thursday.
