<HEAD>EEC Sees Continued Strong Demand for Common Market Steel</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The EEC Commission forecasted Friday
that second-quarter crude steel production in the 12-nation trade
bloc would total 35 million metric tons, the same as the current
quarter.
   The forecast, though was up slightly from 34.5 million tons in
the second quarter of 1988.
   Steel production in the trade bloc rose 9 percent in 1988 to
137.2 million tons as demand for steel was boosted by a strong
performance of the EEC economy.
   The Commission said demand for steel in the automobile and
construction industries remained strong so far this year.
