<FIRST>r f BC-TradeMeet     03-10 0149</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Trade Meet,0155</SECOND>
<HEAD>San Francisco To Host Trade Conference with Soviets</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   San Francisco will host a high-level
Soviet-U.S. trade conference May 23 that will focus on the
development of trade between the West Coast and the Soviet Far East.
   Mayor Art Agnos said Thursday the event likely will include
Soviet delegates at the Politburo level.
   He called the conference ``an opportunity to give glasnost a
human face and a personal touch for participants throughout the
Western United States.''
   Agnos said the conference would draw high-ranking regional
business experts and scientific experts from both the United States
and the Soviet Union. It will be the highest-level trade delegation
to visit the United States since former Premier Nikita Khrushchev's
1959 visit, he said.
   Corporate sponsors of the conference include AT&amp;T, Levi Strauss,
Bank of America, Bechtel Group, Chevron, Syntex Corp., Wells Fargo
Bank and Shaklee Corp.
</TEXT>
