<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fixed-rate home mortgages are currently
averaging 10.86 percent, according to a national survey released
Friday by the Federal Home Loan Mortgage Corp.
   That rate was down from a rate of 10.91 percent last week.
   On one-year adjustable-rate mortgages, lenders were asking an
average initial rate of 8.93 percent this week, up from 8.91 percent
the week before, Freddie Mac said.
