<HEAD>Oil Prices Mixed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The energy futures market turned mixed in choppy
trading Friday, with prices of wholesale home heating oil and
gasoline rising and crude oil falling.
   The April contract for heating oil gained 0.81 cent to settle at
51.19 cents a gallon on the New York Mercantile Exhange, after
declining 0.99 cent on Thursday.
   April unleaded gasoline, which fell 0.25 cent Thursday, closed up
0.18 cent on the exchange to 51.78 cents a gallon.
   The April contract for West Texas Intermediate, the benchmark
grade of U.S. crude oil, closed at $18.50 a barrel, down 2 cents.
The contract had fallen 2 cents in the previous session.
   Most of Friday's activity was focused on gasoline, market
observers said.
   William Byers, an energy analyst with Bear, Stearns &amp; Co., said
prices had risen in anticipation of an Environmental Protection
Agency report on summer gasoline standards.
   He said the report, released after the market closed, proposed
changes in gasoline chemical composition that may push up refining
costs, and, ultimately gas prices.
</TEXT>
