<FILEID>AP-NR-03-10-89 2028EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>u f AM-Emhart     03-10 0222</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Emhart,0231</SECOND>
<HEAD>Topper Offers to Enter Into Confidentiality Agreement; Emhart Rejects
It</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The investor group seeking to buy Emhart Corp.
offered Friday to enter into a confidentiality agreement with the
consumer and industrial products manufacturer, but Emhart dismissed
the offer as unacceptable.
   Topper L.P. said in a statement it was willing to enter into an
agreement under which Emhart would give the investor group access to
confidential financial information about the company. Topper has
offered to buy Emhart for $35 a share or a total of $2.4 billion.
   However, the statement made no mention of a standstill agreement,
which Emhart has insisted Topper sign before it can see the
information. Under a standstill agreement, investors say they will
not acquire any further stock in a target company except through a
tender offer.
   Emhart, which has rejected the Topper bid as inadequate, said the
investor group ``has not indicated to Emhart that it is willing to
sign a confidentiality and standstill agreement in a form
acceptable'' to the manufacturer.
   Therefore, Emhart said, it was not agreeing to supply information
to Topper.
   Emhart says it has supplied information to other parties
interested in buying the company. It has not identified any other
bidders.
   Topper's investors include oil heir Gordon P. Getty and New York
developers Lawrence and Zachary Fisher.

</TEXT>
